      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " قَالَ أَبُو عَبْدِ اللَّهِ ( عليه السلام ) إِنَّ الْفُحْشَ وَ الْبَذَاءَ وَ السَّلَاطَةَ مِنَ النِّفَاقِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad, from Muhammad Bin Sinan, from Ibn Muskan, from Al Hassan al Sayqal who said, ",
          "‘Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘The immorality, and the obscenity, and the insolence are from the hypocrisy’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "10. Muhammad ibn Yahya has narrated from Ahmad ibn Muhammad from Muhammad ibn Sinan from ibn Muskan from al-Hassan al-Sayqal who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah (a.s.) has said, abusive, foul language and a sharp tongue is hypocrisy.’” "
        ]
      }
